{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q839110]] Wikidata name: 18th day of the 3rd month in the Chinese calendar [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 08:00, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Not to be confused with|March 18|qq=March 18}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月十八|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 18일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 18''' is the 18th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|qid=Q96759840}}{{efn|ja|友引|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}{{efn|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Kenchō|Kenchō]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1249|1249]] [[:en:May 2|May 2]]) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Hōji (era)|Hōji]] to [[:en:Kenchō|Kenchō]]. * [[:en:Man'en|Man'en]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1860|1860]] [[:en:April 8|April 8]]) – Due to the occurrence of the [[:en:Sakuradamon Incident (1860)|Sakuradamon Incident]], the era name was changed from [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] to [[:en:Man'en|Man'en]].
== Births == * [[:en:Genkō (1321–1324)|Genki (era)]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1573|1573]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – [[:en:Doi Toshikatsu|Doi Toshikatsu]], Tairō and the first daimyō of the Furukawa Domain in Kazusa (died [[:en:1644|1644]]). * [[:en:Shunji|Shunji]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1654|1654]] [[:en:May 4|May 4]]) – [[:en:Kangxi Emperor|Kangxi Emperor]], the 4th Emperor of the Qing dynasty (died [[:en:1722|1722]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Civilization|Bunmei]] 5th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1473|1473]] [[:en:April 15|April 15]]) – [[:en:Yamana Sōzen|Yamana Sōzen]] (also known as Yamana Mochitoyo) – a regional warlord (born [[:en:1404|1404]]).
